<!-- 
This will form the card collection within the game. It will allow for the easy addition of 
more cards into the game by simply adding a new <Card> and populating it with the relevant data

Ability types will determine how a given card will act within the combat round of the game. 

Ability Types : 
				Damage (Basic attack) 
				SurpriseAttack (Extra Damage if the card acts before target)
				Rampage (If card kills target enemy attack another target)
				DamageOverTime (Extra damage at the start of the following round)
				Enlarge (Double Damage, but takes an additional space on the board)
				Evasion (Avoid all damage this round)
				ForcedTarget (selected cards must target selected card with abilities)
				Disabled (Unable to attack next round)
				Stunnded (Unable to act this round)
				Grappled (Selected cards deal half damage)
				Slowed (Target Acts slower for a number of rounds)

In addition the ability types the abilities will also have a target type; this will determine 
how targets are selected for abilities. 

Target Types : 
				Self (This card is selected for the ability target)
				Single (One card is selected)
				Multiple (Two cards are selected)
				AllEnemy (All opponents cards are selected)
				All (All cards on both sides of the board are selected)
				RandomEnemy (A random target is selected from all enemies)
				RandomAlly (A random target is selected from player's own cards)
				RandomAll (A random target is selected from all cards on the board)
-->

